{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Setting up an Xcode project that uses MapLibre Native for iOS."}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"metadata":{"role":"article","modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"Getting Started","roleHeading":"Article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Create a new iOS project","level":2,"anchor":"Create-a-new-iOS-project","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create a new (SwiftUI) iOS project with Xcode. Go to ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"File > New > Project…","type":"text"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Add MapLibre Native as a dependency","level":2,"anchor":"Add-MapLibre-Native-as-a-dependency","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"MapLibre Native for iOS is available on "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/cocoapods.org"},{"type":"text","text":" and on the "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/swiftpackageindex.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-gl-native-distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" (for use with the Swift Package Manager). However, for this guide we will add the MapLibre Native as a package dependency directly."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In Xcode, right click your project and select “Add Package Dependencies…”:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"image","identifier":"AddPackageDependencies.png"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Paste the following URL and click Add Package:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-gl-native-distribution"],"type":"codeListing"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-gl-native-distribution"},{"type":"text","text":" repository only exists for distributing the iOS package of MapLibre Native. To report issues and ask questions, use the "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native"},{"type":"text","text":" repository."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Verify you can import MapLibre in your app:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["import MapLibre"],"type":"codeListing"},{"text":"SwiftUI","level":2,"anchor":"SwiftUI","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To use MapLibre with SwiftUI we need to create a wrapper for the UIKit view that MapLibre provides (using UIViewRepresentable. The simplest way to implement this protocol is as follows:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct SimpleMap: UIViewRepresentable {","    func makeUIView(context _: Context) -> MLNMapView {","        let mapView = MLNMapView()","        return mapView","    }","","    func updateUIView(_: MLNMapView, context _: Context) {}","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use this view directly in a SwiftUI View hierarchy, for example:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["struct MyApp: App {","    var body: some Scene {","        WindowGroup {","            SimpleMap().edgesIgnoringSafeArea(.all)","        }","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When running your app in the simulator you should be greeted with the default "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/demotiles.maplibre.org\/"},{"type":"text","text":" style:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"DemotilesScreenshot.png","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"UIKit","level":2,"anchor":"UIKit","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use the following "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UIViewController"},{"type":"text","text":" to get started with MapLibre Native iOS with UIKit."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"synt